; Regression test for issue #1565: Precision specified with D being ignored (BZ#493)
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/1565
;
; The D directive sets the default commodity and its format (precision, separators).
; When bare (uncommoditized) amounts are used, the D directive commodity and precision
; should be applied.  Tests both commodity assignment and precision preservation.

D $1,000.00

2024/01/01 Whole amount
    Expenses:Food    100
    Assets:Cash     -100

2024/02/01 Fractional amount
    Expenses:Drink    50.10
    Assets:Cash

test bal
            $-150.10  Assets:Cash
             $150.10  Expenses
              $50.10    Drink
             $100.00    Food
--------------------
                   0
end test

test reg Expenses
24-Jan-01 Whole amount          Expenses:Food               $100.00      $100.00
24-Feb-01 Fractional amount     Expenses:Drink               $50.10      $150.10
end test
